fish.definition: A cold-blooded vertebrate animal that lives in water, moving with the help of fins and breathing with gills.

dog.definition: A mammal, Canis familiaris or Canis lupus familiaris, that has been domesticated for thousands of years, of highly variable appearance due to human breeding.

tree.definition: Fast growing function based on Kruskal's tree theorem.
